<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="133" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">
The type species of the new genus is 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Branchiomma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Branchiomma koellikeri" order="Sabellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="133" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="koellikeri">Branchiomma koellikeri</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
, 1869 (junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Sabella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sabella lanigera" order="Sabellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="133" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lanigera">Sabella lanigera</taxonomicName>
Grube, 1846), according to recommendation 60A of the 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, W" journalOrPublisher="The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" title="International Code of Zoological Nomenclature" url="http://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.50608" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. Type by monotypy, established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Johansson, KE" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv foer Zoologi" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" pagination="1 - 28" title="Bemerkungen ueber die Kinberg'schen Arten der Familien Hermellidae und Sabellidae" url="http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=sourcedetails&amp;id=50543" volume="18 A" year="1926">Johansson (1926)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="133" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">
Following his principle of basing observations and descriptions only on live organisms 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Édouard">Edouard</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
did not designate type material or deposit specimens in museums or collections (
<bibRefCitation author="Fauchald, K" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="11" pageNumber="142" pagination="742 - 752" title="The Second Annual Riser Lecture: eclectism and the study of polychaetes." url="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/34551126" volume="102" year="1989">Fauchald 1989</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Knight-Jones, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" pagination="313 - 323" title="Two new species of Megalomma (Sabellidae) from Sinai and New Zealand with redescriptions of some types and a new genus." url="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/contentone/umrsmas/bullmar/1997/00000060/00000002/art00013" volume="60" year="1997">Knight-Jones (1997)</bibRefCitation>
refers the existence of a type of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Branchiomma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Branchiomma koellikeri" order="Sabellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="133" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="koellikeri">Branchiomma koellikeri</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
, 1869 deposited at the Zoological Museum of Berlin (currently the Museum 
<normalizedToken originalValue="für">fuer</normalizedToken>
Naturkunde Berlin), with the reference number ZMB 6387. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tovar-Hernandez, MA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="146" pagination="1 - 71" title="Megalomma Johansson, 1925 (Polychaeta: Sabellidae) from America and other world-wide localities, and phylogenetic relationships within the genus." url="http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/list/2011/2861.html" volume="2861" year="2011">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tovar-Hernández">Tovar-Hernandez</normalizedToken>
and Carrera-Parra (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
refer this specimen as being a syntype. Although the designation of a lectotype for 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. koellikeri" pageId="2" pageNumber="133" rank="species" species="koellikeri">B. koellikeri</taxonomicName>
is desirable, it is out of the scope of the present work.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="133" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">
The name of the new genus is composed by combining the Greek terms for acro, meaning &quot;tip end&quot; or &quot;extremity of a body&quot;, mega, meaning 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“big”">&quot;big&quot;</normalizedToken>
or 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“large”">&quot;large&quot;</normalizedToken>
, and the suffix -omma, a noun meaning 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“eye”">&quot;eye&quot;</normalizedToken>
, and referring to the big compound eyes located on the radiolar subdistal region, typical of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="133" type="gender">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">Gender.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">Neuter.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="2" pageNumber="133" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="133">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="2" pageNumber="133">
The publication date of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Megalomma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megalomma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megalomma</taxonomicName>
Johansson should be considered as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1926”">&quot;1926&quot;</normalizedToken>
. It was generally accepted as being 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1927”">&quot;1927&quot;</normalizedToken>
until 
<bibRefCitation author="Tovar-Hernandez, MA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="146" pagination="1951 - 1973" title="Caruncle in Megalomma Johansson, 1925 (Polychaeta: Sabellidae) and the description of a new species from the Eastern Tropical Pacific." url="http://doi.org/10.1080/00222930802140186" volume="42" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tovar-Hernández">Tovar-Hernandez</normalizedToken>
and Salazar-Vallejo (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that the name had been introduced in a previous publication by the same author, referring the date as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1925”">&quot;1925&quot;</normalizedToken>
. In fact, the last page of this publication states &quot;Tryckt den 5 november 1925&quot; (&quot;Printed the 5 November 1925&quot;) and in the following line &quot; 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="134" start="start">Uppsala</pageBreakToken>
1925. Almquist &amp; Wiksells Boktryckeri-A.-B.&quot; This date is also present in existing reprints of the paper. However, the bounded volume comprising the article provides the publication date as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Häfte">&quot;Haefte</normalizedToken>
2 inneh. A N:o 6-12, [...] utkom den 5 juni 1926&quot; (&quot;Booklet 2 cont. A No. 6-12, [...] published 5 June 1926&quot;). This booklet includes article 7A by Johansson, where the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Megalomma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megalomma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megalomma</taxonomicName>
is introduced for polychaetes. Hence, the work was printed in 5 November 1925, but published only in the following year, on 5 June 1926.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="134">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Acromegalomma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acromegalomma" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Acromegalomma</taxonomicName>
, nomen novum is represented by 36 valid species, all of them new combinations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
